name: Suśīlā-Bīrsiṃha : nāṭak : Sekspiyar kr̥ta nāṭak biśesh abalamvana kariyā biracita.
alternateName: Cymbeline. Bengali, Sushila-Birsingha, Sushila Bir Singha, Sushila O Birsingha, Sushila-Virshingha
description: Author widely known in English as Satyendranath Tagore. Adaptation of Shakespeare's Cymbeline, in Bengali. See Ahsan, N. Shakespeare translations in nineteenth-century Bengali theatre, p. 33. Signatures: pi² [1]⁴ 2-22⁴ 23⁶. Also available as a digital reproduction.
disambiguatingDescription: In quarter calf with marbled paper boards; gilt title and tooling on spine; marbled endpapers; publisher’s printed wrapper. Stamp: Edward Dowden Library. Manuscript bibliographical note tipped in.
